repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body: After removing Python 2 support, there is no difference between "3" and "3str" any more, so "3str" becomes an alias.

commit.message: Replace "language_level=3str" with "language_level=3" since "3str" is useless outside of Python 2.
Allow ASCII Unicode strings to coerce to char* and char since they often originate from unprefixed strings in language_level=3.
Fix accepted type of @cname() decorator since we now receive unicode strings.
Directly set language_level=3 when passing the "--3str" CLI option.
Fix a test after allowing conversion of ASCII text strings to char*.
Fix a test after changing "str" to "unicode" in language_level=3.
See if we can switch to language_level=3 for the Cython modules build.
Remove the redundant "language_level" directives from the Cython source files.
Generally disable the "auto_pickle" directive for the Cython build to save module space, unless explicitly requested/needed.

commit.message: Remove the redundant "auto_pickle" directives from the Cython source files.
Allow Unicode strings to coerce also to (encoded) C++ strings and use the "c_string_encoding" (if provided) to encode the string if it doesn't have a parsed bytes value.
